#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:4
msgid ":index:`Download & Install Picard <install; download>`"
msgstr ":index:`Picard downloaden en installeren <installeren; downloaden>`"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:6
msgid ""
"MusicBrainz Picard is available for all major desktop operating systems (e."
"g. Windows, Linux and macOS), and in multiple forms (directly downloadable "
"formal release executables, package manager versions of these, daily build "
"executables, Python source code that you can execute with your own Python "
"environment, etc.)"
msgstr ""
"MusicBrainz Picard is beschikbaar voor alle grote pc-besturingssystemen "
"(zoals Windows, Linux en macOS) en in verschillende vormen (officiële en "
"rechtstreeks te downloaden uitvoerbare bestanden, versies hiervan voor "
"pakketbeheerders, dagelijkse builds, Python-broncode die je in je eigen "
"Python-omgeving kan uitvoeren enz.)."

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:8
msgid ""
"It is expected that most users will run formal release executables or "
"package manager equivalents as these are easy to install, and are stable "
"versions which are less likely to have bugs in experimental or new "
"functionality."
msgstr ""
"De meeste gebruikers zullen de officiële versies of de equivalenten daarvan "
"uit pakketbeheerders gebruiken, want die zijn makkelijk te installeren en "
"stabieler dan experimentele versies die nieuwe functies maar ook bugs hebben."

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:10
msgid ""
"However, any users wishing to contribute to the development of Picard or its "
"Plugins may want to run from source code, downloading it from GitHub using a "
"version of Git on their own computer. If you want to contribute to the "
"Picard code but you don't understand what the previous sentence said, then "
"you have a bit of a learning curve. :-)"
msgstr ""
"Maar als gebruikers aan de ontwikkeling van Picard of zijn plug-ins willen "
"bijdragen, willen ze Picard misschien vanuit de broncode draaien. Daarvoor "
"moeten ze de broncode met een versie van Git uit GitHub naar hun computer "
"downloaden. Als je aan de code van Picard wil bijdragen maar de vorige zin "
"niet begrijpt, heb je nog wat te leren. :-)"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:12
msgid ""
"The latest version of MusicBrainz Picard is always available for download "
"from the `Picard Website <https://picard.musicbrainz.org/downloads/>`_. This "
"includes installers for all supported platforms as well as `release source "
"code <https://picard.musicbrainz.org/downloads/#source>`_. The very latest "
"source code is also available at the `GitHub repository <https://github.com/"
"musicbrainz/picard>`_."
msgstr ""
"Je kan de nieuwste versie van Picard altijd van de `website van Picard "
"<https://picard.musicbrainz.org/downloads/>`_ downloaden. Je vindt er onder "
"andere installatieprogramma’s voor alle ondersteunde platformen en de "
"`broncode van uitgaveversies <https://picard.musicbrainz.org/downloads/"
"#source>`_. De nieuwste broncode is ook te vinden in de `GitHub-opslagplaats "
"<https://github.com/musicbrainz/picard>`_."

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:16
msgid "Installing Picard on Linux"
msgstr "Picard op Linux installeren"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:19
msgid ":index:`Installing with Flatpak <pair: install; flatpak>`"
msgstr ":index:`Met een Flatpak installeren <pair: installeren; flatpak>`"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:21
msgid ""
"Picard is available on `Flathub <https://flathub.org/apps/details/org."
"musicbrainz.Picard>`_. This version should work on all modern Linux "
"distributions, as long as Flatpak is installed (see `Flatpak Quick Setup "
"<https://flatpak.org/setup/>`_)."
msgstr ""
"Picard is beschikbaar op `Flathub <https://flathub.org/apps/details/"
"org.musicbrainz.Picard>`_. Deze versie zou op elke moderne Linux-distributie "
"moeten werken, mits Flatpak is geïnstalleerd (zie `Flatpak Quick Setup "
"<https://flatpak.org/setup/>`_)."

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:23
msgid "First enable the Flathub repository:"
msgstr "Eerst moet je de Flathub-opslagplaats inschakelen:"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:29
msgid "You can now install Picard:"
msgstr "Vervolgens kan je Picard installeren:"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:37
msgid ":index:`Installing with Snap <pair: install; snap>`"
msgstr ":index:`Met Snap installeren <pair: installeren; snap>`"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:39
msgid ""
"Picard is available as a Snap from the Snap Store. This version should work "
"on all modern Linux distributions, as long as Snap is installed (see "
"`Installing Snap <https://snapcraft.io/docs/installing-snapd>`_)."
msgstr ""
"Picard is als Snap-pakket in de Snap Store beschikbaar. Deze versie zou op "
"elke moderne Linux-distributie moeten werken, mits Snap is geïnstalleerd "
"(zie `Install the daemon <https://snapcraft.io/docs/installing-snapd>`_)."

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:41
msgid ""
"The `Snap Store page of Picard <https://snapcraft.io/picard>`_ gives "
"detailed instructions on how to install Picard on various Linux "
"distributions. If your Linux distributions supports it you can install "
"Picard from your distribution's software center, e.g. Ubuntu Software or KDE "
"Discover. You can also install Picard from the terminal:"
msgstr ""
"Op de `pagina over Picard in de Snap Store <https://snapcraft.io/picard>`_ "
"vind je informatie over het installeren van Picard op verschillende Linux-"
"distributies. Als je Linux-distributie dit ondersteunt, kan je Picard "
"installeren vanuit het softwarecentrum van je distributie, zoals Ubuntu "
"Software of KDE Discover. Je kan Picard ook via de terminal installeren:"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:49
msgid ""
"Picard installed as a Snap is running inside a sandbox and thus it does not "
"have full access to all files and folders on your system. By default Picard "
"has access to your home folder. You can additionally give it access to "
"removable media by running the following command on a terminal:"
msgstr ""
"Als Picard als Snap is geïnstalleerd, draait hij in een zandbak en heeft hij "
"geen volledige toegang tot alle bestanden en mappen op je systeem. Picard "
"heeft standaard alleen toegang tot je thuismap. Je kan Picard toegang tot "
"verwijderbare media geven met de volgende terminalopdracht:"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:57
msgid ""
":index:`Installing from your distribution's package repository <pair: "
"install; Linux package>`"
msgstr ""
":index:`Picard vanuit de pakketopslag van je distributie installeren <pair: "
"installeren; Linux-pakket>`"

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:59
msgid ""
"Picard is available in the package repositories of most distributions. The "
"`download page <https://picard.musicbrainz.org/downloads/#linux>`_ provides "
"links to the packages for common Linux distributions. Please refer to your "
"distribution's documentation for how to install software packages."
msgstr ""
"Picard is in de pakketopslag van de meeste distributies beschikbaar. Op de "
"`downloadpagina <https://picard.musicbrainz.org/downloads/#linux>`_ vind je "
"links naar de pakketten voor bekende Linux-distributies. In de documentatie "
"van je distributie kan je lezen hoe je softwarepakketten installeert."

#: ../../getting_started/download.rst:61
msgid ""
"Please note that most distributions usually ship older versions of Picard. "
"If you want to use the latest available version, as is recommended, install "
"Picard as Flatpak or Snap as described above."
msgstr ""
"Houd er rekening mee dat distributies vaak oudere versies van Picard hebben. "
"Als je de nieuwste versie wil gebruiken (wat we aanraden), kan je Picard als "
"Flatpak of Snap installeren."
